From a biological perspective, this two-parameter diagram encapsulates the critical management regimes for controlling Nosema ceranae. Colonies operating below the Hopf boundary represent resilient systems capable of maintaining stable endemic infection levels, whereas those above the boundary are vulnerable to cyclic outbreaks and possible collapse. The \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
